From: Northeastern Graduate Admissions - DO NOT REPLY <global@northeastern.edu>
Subject: You are invited‚Äîlearn how to build a thriving career
Body:
Join Northeastern's virtual open house on March 17--18.
Hi Amrutha Sridhanya,
Ready to take your career to the next level? Get to know Northeastern University and learn about the advantages of earning your graduate degree at a top-tier U.S. university. We have planned two days filled with virtual events to provide you with all the information and advice you need to shape your future.
Meet Northeastern faculty, staff, and students at our Virtual Graduate Open House <https://ter.li/oh-int-inv-s26> on March 17--18. As you continue to work on your application, we will have more information to share that will help you to understand the many advantages Northeastern offers you. The webinar will give you confidence that you are making the right choice for your future. We will have support available to help you complete your application, and our college and student support teams will provide any assistance you need to ease the process.
REGISTER NOW <https://ter.li/oh-int-inv-s26>
On both days, you will be able to:
Get acquainted with the benefits of Northeastern's focus on experiential learning, its No. 1-ranked co-op program, and its global campus network.
Join live college overview, program-specific, and student support sessions.
Meet faculty with expert industry experience who are passionate about your success.
Chat with staff and learn about scholarship opportunities and how we support your Northeastern education from application through graduation.
Connect with alumni and current students and learn about their Northeastern experience.
Virtually sit with global enrollment counselors in personalized one-on-one drop-in meetings.
Learn about our international network of campuses across the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom.
We hope you will join us and take advantage of this opportunity to see how Northeastern can help you achieve your personal and professional goals. It's your chance to explore our community.
You are in charge of how you spend your time. Whether you attend one or more live sessions or explore on-demand videos in your available time, we look forward to meeting you.
Register here <https://ter.li/oh-int-inv-s26> to secure your spot.
Sincerely,
Northeastern Graduate Admissions
Northeastern University

You‚Äôre invited to a fast‚Äëpaced introduction to Microsoft 365 Copilot at work. You‚Äôll learn what it is, how it grounds answers in your organization‚Äôs data via Microsoft Graph, and where it shows up in Word, Outlook, Teams, and more ‚Äî with quick demos.
We‚Äôll also show how Copilot and Azure Course Blueprints streamline the Azure certification journey. You‚Äôll see how Copilot summarizes Microsoft Learn modules, answers domain questions, and turns the Blueprints into a personalized, trackable study plan. We‚Äôll close with next steps and optional training paths.
When: Thursday, February 5, 2026 at 9 a.m. PT/12 p.m. ET
Registration for this webinar is free.
Register now
About the speaker
Ilan Nyska is a Microsoft Technical Trainer focused on Azure architecture and security. He created the Azure Course Blueprints, a widely adopted learning resource with 44,000+ downloads in its first year, and has trained and mentored thousands across Microsoft‚Äôs certification programs, including MSSA cohorts. He brings a practitioner‚Äôs lens to demystify cloud design and help learners move from concepts to implementation quickly.

Subject: 1 more week until the deadline
Body:
Dear MDS V applicant,
Just a quick note that there is only 1 more week until our international student deadline (January 31) for the UBC Master of Data Science program. This is also the deadline for Canadian and US applicants who want to be considered for our scholarships<https://masterdatascience.ubc.ca/admissions/tuition-and-financial-aid> (see more details about deadlines here<https://mds.ubc.ca/admissions>). If you have any last minute questions, please do not hesitate to reach out:
1. Email our general inbox at info-mds@science.ubc.ca<mailto:info-mds@science.ubc.ca>.
2. Attend one of our Zoom drop in sessions which happen every Wednesday, until February 11, from 1-2pm. Here is the Zoom link: https://ubc.zoom.us/j/69372091723?pwd=adfVRArf9LbrIYuLqEaZJ4qKHV8RP3.1. Please read the participant guidelines here: https://mds.ubc.ca/contact-us (a way to meet with our Program Manager or Senior Program Assistant).
3. Email me. As the Director, Program Operations and Student Management, I am happy to answer any questions you may have.
Looking forward to hearing from you.
Best regards,
Milad Maymay (He, Him)
Director, Program Operations & Student Management
Master of Data Science ‚Äì Vancouver Campus
Faculty of Science
The University of British Columbia
Phone: 604 822 4217
maymay@science.ubc.ca<mailto:maymay@science.ubc.ca>
https://masterdatascience.ubc.ca

Subject: Build Intelligent AI Agents | Applied Agentic AI Program | Simplilearn & Microsoft
Body:
Hi Amrutha,
Ever wondered how the tech stack behind AI agents actually works? What‚Äôs happening in the backend when those agents plan, learn, and collaborate?
The
Applied Agentic AI: Systems, Design & Impact
program delivered by Simplilearn, in partnership with Microsoft is designed to help you understand that stack and build intelligent Agentic systems capable of autonomous decision-making and solving complex AI challenges.
Why Should You Join This Program?
Agentic AI‚ÄìFirst Curriculum
Master agentic AI systems, planning frameworks, multi-agent ecosystems, and product strategy in a 10-week, practitioner-level program
Optional Python Refresher
Brush up on Python essentials and AI-ready workflows before diving into the core Agentic AI courses
Real-World Learning
Apply your learning through 40+ demos, 10+ guided practices, 11 frameworks, 9 hands-on course-end projects, and 1 capstone
16+ In-Demand Skills
Develop expertise in Agentic frameworks, multi-agent systems, RAG,
MCP, planning systems, workflow automation, GTM for Agentic AI, UX
design, and product readiness‚Äîall focused on real-world application
Hands-On With 16+ Tools
Work with leading tools like LangChain, AutoGen, CrewAI, n8n, Emergent, Lovable, Figma, LangSmith, Jupyter, and more
Immersive Live Learning Experience
Join live, online interactive classes led by industry experts and
Microsoft-certified trainers with peer-to-peer engagement on Slack,
mentoring sessions, and dedicated cohort support
Industry-Recognized Credentials
Earn a joint program completion certificate from Microsoft and Simplilearn, plus Microsoft Learn badges on the Microsoft Learn portal for the Microsoft-branded courses
Career Assistance
Get resume reviews, interview tips, and profile guidance through Simplilearn‚Äôs career assistance to showcase your Agentic AI skills
Lead the next wave of AI innovation. Build multi-agent ecosystems, design autonomous workflows, and shape the future of intelligent products.

Subject: Lessons in leadership from MLK Jr.
Body:
On the third Monday of January, we honor the life and legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., a transformative figure whose lessons in civil rights and leadership continue to resonate across politics, policy, and global change.
Explore the principles he championed with courses that cover the core areas of his life‚Äôs work.
Discover courses
Politics
Dr. King's non-violent approach was a powerful political strategy and his life shows us how individuals can influence elections, legislation, and public opinion. Study the mechanisms of US and international politics, from grassroots organizing to global diplomacy, and learn how you can effectively bring about change.
Weekly course features
Policy
The Civil Rights Act and Voting Rights Act are testaments to King‚Äôs ability to turn a movement into concrete policy change. Explore how public and international policies are developed, and learn skills to analyze complex policy issues, advocate for reform, and lead real-world outcomes in your community and beyond.
Leadership
King's leadership was defined by moral authority, resilience, and a clear vision for a better world. Discover the essential skills of global leadership that can be applied in any field, from business to non-profits to government.
We want to hear from you
This year edX is reaching an incredible milestone: 100 million learners worldwide. But this moment isn‚Äôt about a number. It‚Äôs about people like you: individuals who have invested in transforming their lives through education.
We‚Äôd like to invite you to be part of our celebration by sharing a short video describing how online learning has changed your life.
There‚Äôs no script and no pressure. We‚Äôre simply asking you to speak from your experience in your own words.
Record your response
Download the edX app
Experience the knowledge and experience of veteran professors directly from your phone.

Subject: Amrutha Sridhanya, you're accepted to New Jersey Institute of Technology - Fall 2026
Body:
Dear Amrutha Sridhanya:
Congratulations! We are pleased to inform you that you have been accepted to the Master of Science in Artificial Intelligence at New Jersey Institute of Technology for the Fall 2026 semester, which begins on September 1, 2026. We're excited to welcome you to the NJIT community!
Please read your next steps below fully and carefully.
1. Submit your deposit.
To secure your spot, you must submit the $500 non-refundable tuition deposit as soon as possible <http://tuitiondeposit.njit.edu/?utm_campaign=DECISION_CAMPAIGN_QA_CRT_202210&utm_content=admission_details&utm_medium=email&utm_source=email_admission&utm_term=202210>. This is required to create your UCID and begin the I-20 request process.
The deposit deadline is May 1, 2026. It is in your best interest to submit your deposit as soon as possible to save your spot and allow time to complete the visa process. You will not be able to progress to the next step of the admission process until you submit your deposit.
Information about requesting your I-20 and submitting additional documentation will be shared with you after you submit your deposit.
This email serves as your official proof of admission for external funding or scholarship applications until we receive your deposit and issue your final acceptance letter.
2. Learn more about cost, employment and scholarships.
You must have available funding (sponsor(s) or yourself) for the first year. The expected amount is USD $68,261 for graduate students. This figure is a conservative planning estimate including tuition, fees and living expenses. Actual per-credit charges vary by your course load, program and living choices. Any merit award you receive reduces the funding required by the award amount. See the estimated tuition breakdown <https://www.njit.edu/admissions/tuition-costs?utm_campaign=DECISION_CAMPAIGN_QA_CRT_202210&utm_content=admission_details&utm_medium=email&utm_source=email_admission&utm_term=202210> under "International Cost of Attendance."
You can learn more about employment opportunities for international students here <https://www.njit.edu/global/employment-f-1-students?utm_campaign=DECISION_CAMPAIGN_QA_CRT_202210&utm_content=admission_details&utm_medium=email&utm_source=email_admission&utm_term=202210>.
If you qualify for a merit award, you'll be notified in a separate email within 1--2 weeks. No request is needed on your part.
3. Connect with your future classmates.
Keep an eye out for an email in the near future with login information for Campus Community, where you will be able to connect with your future classmates!
If you have any questions, feel free to contact your admissions counselor Tyrone Foster at tyrone.l.foster@njit.edu or at +1 973-596-5311.
We look forward to finalizing your admission and welcoming you to NJIT!
Sincerely,
Cory A. Cottingim
Director of Graduate and International Admissions
Office of University Admissions
New Jersey Institute of Technology
University Heights, Newark, New Jersey 07102
973-596-3300
njit.edu | admissions@njit.edu

Subject: January Updates: ‚ú® Smarter AI Reviews, Better Citations + 60% Off
Body:
We're delighted to bring you the latest updates from Paperpal.
Over the past few weeks, we've shipped several new features and meaningful enhancements, each designed to make your research writing faster, clearer, and more confident. Keep reading to see what's new. Don't miss your personalized December usage summary at the end.
Before you dive in, a quick reminder that our Republic Day Sale is live right now, with
60% off
end-to-end academic writing support
. Don't miss this chance to make 2026 your most productive, successful year yet!
üéØ Get actionable insights with in-depth AI reviews
Paperpal's
AI Review
tool now does more than offer instant, expert-level insights on your manuscript: it tells you exactly
what
needs to change and
how
.
Responses are more
detailed
, more
actionable
, and come with clear before and after versions, making it easier to apply the suggestions.
We've also updated the list of pre-set prompts to align better with academic and publication needs. For example, if you're looking for journal peer reviewer-style feedback, just choose ‚Äú
Expert Peer Reviewer Feedback (Journal-Style)
‚Äù from the list.
üóÇÔ∏è Add non-indexed citations to Paperpal
Not all research sources are indexed in academic databases. Examples include government drafts, corporate reports, datasets, and unpublished theses. Yet these sources still need to be cited accurately.
With the recent upgrade to our citation workflow, you can now
add these sources manually and cite them automatically
, in your selected style, across both MS Word and Paperpal‚Äôs online editor. Not just add, you can also edit citations on Paperpal.
üîç Introducting Paperpal's AI Detector
As AI plays a bigger role in academia, academic writing is changing to become more hybrid in style. That's why binary verdicts like "Human-written" or "AI-written" don't tell the full story.
Paperpal's homegrown AI detector is designed for
more nuanced analysis
of hybrid academic writing.
Instead of giving out an opaque verdict, Paperpals' AI detector analyzes your writing
sentence by sentence
and classifies each one into three clear categories‚Äî
Human-written
,
Human‚ÄìAI blend
, or
AI-written
. Each category offers clear insight and direction on what to do next, helping you submit your work with clarity and confidence.
‚ûï Write better with support for more reference files
Paperpal's all-new
Write
tool makes it easier than ever to start writing. Just upload your reference files, and
Write
will extract insights, connect ideas, and get you to a coherent first draft in minutes.
With the latest update, you get:
The ability to upload up to 5 reference files per conversation (up from 3)
Support for more file formats, including PDF, DOCX, XLSX, CSV, PPTX, JPG, JPEG, TIF, WEBP, and GIF
Context retained throughout the conversation
Conversation history preserved, so you can come back anytime and pick up where you left off
üí° Brainstorm ideas and refine them in flow
Brainstorming doesn't have to stop at the first good idea.
With the new conversational flow inside the
Brainstorm
feature, you can keep the chat going‚Äîask follow ups, expand on the previous idea, or start a new ideating session.
Use
Brainstorm
to chat with Paperpal AI and refine your thoughts before you start writing.
üìÑ Work with larger files (up to 25 MB)
Paperpal‚Äôs online editor now supports files up to 25 MB (up from 10 MB).
If you‚Äôre working on a thesis or any other large document, or checking a large file for plagiarism, you can now upload and work with it without any difficulty.
We‚Äôre thrilled to share that our parent company,
Cactus Communications (CACTUS)
, has earned the ISO/IEC 42001:2023 certification for its Artificial Intelligence (AI) Management System.
The world‚Äôs first AI management system standard, ISO/IEC 42001:2023 addresses key risks and responsibilities associated with AI‚Äîincluding fairness, reliability, system oversight, and lifecycle management.
This certification applies across all CACTUS brands and solutions, including¬†Paperpal, and validates that CACTUS has established, implemented, and maintains a comprehensive AI governance framework aligned with global best practices.
That's it from us for now. Before we wrap up, here's a quick reminder to check your Paperpal usage summary for December below.
Until next month,
Happy writing!
Team Paperpal
Paperpal & You ‚ô•Ô∏è in December

because when we learn together, we lead together.
Save 15% on select courses and programs when you register before February 5, 2026.

at registration to claim this special offer.
*
*
Offer is valid until February 5, 2026, at 11:59 p.m. Eastern Time (U.S.). Offer does not apply to degree programs. Offer cannot be combined with other discount codes. edX.org
.
Executive education offer is valid on the following universities: SDA Bocconi School of Management, University of Cambridge Institute for Sustainability Leadership, Harvard Online, HEC Paris, IBM, MIT School of Architecture and Planning, MIT Sloan School of Management, Northwestern University, Rice University, Stanford Center for Health Education, the London School of Economics and Political Science, UC Davis Graduate School of Management, University of Cape Town, University of Oxford, and University of Toronto. The offer applies to any start date as long as you register and pay by February 5, 2026. To redeem the offer for executive education courses, register on getsmarter.com, using code DAYOFED2026 at checkout. Subject: Where are Foreign Investors Placing their bets?
Body:
To view this email as a web page, go to the link below, or copy and paste it into your browser's address window.
https://click.communications.sbicapsec.com/?%3D%3D
FPI Fortnightly - January First Half
Dear Investor,
At SBI Securities, we‚Äôre dedicated to providing you with market intelligence to make informed investment decisions. In this email, we‚Äôll explore the influence of Foreign Portfolio Investors (FPIs) on various sectors!!
Here‚Äôs a quick breakdown of the latest FPI Fortnightly data:
What are FPIs, Inflows and Outflows?
‚Ä¢
Foreign Portfolio Investors (FPIs): Overseas investors who invest in Indian stocks, bonds and other financial instruments.
‚Ä¢
Inflows: FPIs investing into the Indian markets by buying.
‚Ä¢
Outflows: FPIs are pulling money out of the Indian markets by selling.
üìà Strong FPI Inflows Seen In:
Foreign Portfolio investors continue to show strong interest in:
‚öôÔ∏è Metals: FPI Momentum Turns Constructive Again
The Metals sector continues to attract strong foreign investor interest. FPIs recorded inflows of ‚Çπ2,689 crore in the first half of January 2026, following ‚Çπ2,984 crore of inflows in December 2025. On a medium-term basis, institutional participation remains firmly constructive, with cumulative net inflows of ‚Çπ5,182 crore during the first nine months of FY26.
From a technical standpoint, Nifty Metal remains positioned in the leading quadrant of the Relative Rotational Graph (RRG), highlighting strong relative strength coupled with improving momentum. The index witnessed a downward-sloping trendline breakout on 12th December, post which it rallied nearly 11% into the first half of January 2026. Importantly, the index continues to trade above key short- and long-term moving averages, reinforcing the bullish structure.
The 11,220‚Äì11,200 zone remains a critical support area. As long as the index sustains above this range, the broader trend is likely to remain bullish.
üõ¢Ô∏è Oil & Gas: Strong FPI Interest, But Technicals Turn Cautious
The Oil & Gas sector has also seen continued foreign buying, with ‚Çπ485 crore of FII inflows in the first half of January 2026, following a robust ‚Çπ18,550 crore inflows during Q3 FY26. This back-to-back accumulation underscores sustained institutional confidence in the sector.
However, the technical picture tells a more cautious story. The Nifty Oil & Gas Index has broken below its key 200-Day EMA at 11,545 on the daily chart. Momentum indicators are weak - the RSI is trending lower and approaching the 30 mark, while the MACD remains below the zero line with rising red histogram bars, signalling bearish momentum.
The 11,540‚Äì11,550 zone (200-Day EMA) is now expected to act as a crucial resistance. The index needs to decisively reclaim this level for any meaningful pullback. Failure to do so could result in prolonged weakness, despite the continued interest from FIIs
üìú Sovereign Bonds: Inflows Resume After Brief Cooling-Off Phase
Foreign investors had been consistent buyers of Indian sovereign bonds since July 2025, with cumulative inflows of ‚Çπ47,068 crore between July and November. This strong accumulation phase saw a temporary pause in December 2025, when FPIs turned net sellers with outflows of ‚Çπ13,613 crore. Encouragingly, the first half of January 2026 has seen renewed buying, with ‚Çπ7,407 crore of inflows, indicating a return of interest.
From a market perspective, the 10-year Indian government bond yield, after retesting its 20-day EMA, has shown steady signs of recovery and is currently trading marginally below its previous swing high of 6.7% recorded on 23rd December 2025. Globally, yields are also on the rise - the US 10-year yield has broken above a horizontal resistance and recently touched 4.31%, while Japanese yields have surged sharply since mid-November, reaching 2.38%.
The simultaneous rise in yields across India, the US, and Japan could enhance the relative attractiveness of bonds and may lead to some reallocation of flows from equities towards fixed income.
üìâ Outflows Continued or Picked Up In:
üè¶ Financial Services: Heavy FPI Selling Meets Technical Breakdown & Unfavourable Seasonality
After FII outflows of ‚Çπ3,532 crore in November, the Financial Services sector witnessed a much sharper sell-off in December 2025, with outflows surging to ‚Çπ15,893 crore, nearly five times the previous month. The selling pressure extended into the new year, with the first half of January 2026 recording further outflows of ‚Çπ3,491 crore, reflecting a cautious and bearish stance from foreign investors.
On the technical front, the Financial Services index has slipped below its 100-Day EMA zone of 27,190‚Äì27,200 on the daily chart, accompanied by a breakdown of the upward-rising trendline. Momentum indicators have weakened, with the DI- crossing above DI+ on the ADX, signalling a shift in momentum in favour of the bears. The RSI has slipped below the 40 mark, underscoring the loss of strength.
Seasonality further adds to the caution. Historically, January has been an unfavourable month for the Financial Services sector, with the index closing in the red in 13 of the last 21 years, delivering an average decline of 0.85%.
üõí FMCG: Sustained FPI Exodus and Support Breakdown Signal Prolonged Weakness
The FMCG sector has remained under persistent FII selling pressure since August 2025. Cumulative outflows over the last five months of 2025 stood at ‚Çπ20,166 crore, with each of the five months witnessing outflows exceeding ‚Çπ4,000 crore. The trend showed no signs of abating in the new year, as the first half of January 2026 saw net outflows of ‚Çπ6,140 crore
From a technical perspective, the 54,200‚Äì54,100 zone, which had been acting as a strong support, was decisively broken on 1st January 2026, after which the index drifted further lower. Seasonality remains unfavourable, with January and February historically weak months, as the index has ended in the red 11 and 13 times respectively out of the last 21 years, delivering average losses of 0.57% and 0.72%.
From a relative strength standpoint, the FMCG sector currently sits in the lagging quadrant of the Relative Rotational Graph (RRG), indicating weak relative performance and subdued momentum. As long as the index trades below the 52,600‚Äì52,700 zone, the overall trend is likely to remain bearish.
üè• Healthcare: Relentless FPI Selling Drives Technical Trend Deterioration
For the first nine months of FY26, the Healthcare sector has witnessed consistent month-on-month FII outflows, with cumulative selling amounting to ‚Çπ19,407 crore. The pressure continued into January 2026, with the first half recording net outflows of ‚Çπ1,066 crore, highlighting relentless foreign selling.
On the technical front, the Nifty Healthcare Index has broken below its 200-Day EMA, accompanied by an upward-sloping trendline breakdown and a negative RSI divergence. The RSI continues to trend lower and is hovering around the 30 mark, while the ADX is rising steadily, suggesting that the bearish trend is strengthening.
The 200-Day EMA zone of 14,400‚Äì14,450 is now expected to act as a crucial resistance area. As long as the index trades below this zone, the overall trend for the sector is likely to remain bearish.
üîÅ Trend Shift Observed:
üíª Telecom: Long FPI Buying Streak Pauses, Early Signs of Momentum Fatigue Emerge
Foreign Portfolio Investors (FPIs) had been consistent net buyers in the Telecom sector since April 2025, with cumulative inflows of ‚Çπ37,006 crore recorded through December 2025. However, the first half of January 2026 marked the first interruption in this buying streak in three months, as FIIs turned net sellers to the extent of ‚Çπ1,497 crore. While the quantum of selling remains modest relative to the strong accumulation seen earlier, the return of FII selling after a prolonged phase of buying is a slightly cautionary development for the sector.
This shift in flows is beginning to reflect in price action across key telecom stocks. Bharti Airtel witnessed a breakdown of its upward-sloping trendline on 9th January, after which the stock has drifted lower and remained under pressure. Momentum indicators have weakened, with the RSI trending lower, while a rising ADX points to strengthening bearish trend intensity. Meanwhile, Vodafone Idea (IDEA), which had seen a strong rally from mid-September 2025 through December, has begun to witness profit booking and is now trading below its key short-term moving averages.
Looking ahead, a renewed bout of FII buying could act as the missing trigger for the sector. Sustained foreign inflows may help arrest the current corrective phase and potentially set the stage for a pullback in the Telecom space.
üìä Attached is a simple infographic summarizing these flows for easy reference.

Subject: Why we waited to build an AI detector, and why we finally did
Body:
Dear amrutha,
For long, we at Paperpal hesitated to build an
AI detector
.
We didn't want another tool that turned academic integrity into a checklist, or worse, encouraged writers to treat AI detection as something to ‚Äúbeat‚Äù. After all, academic writing is about communicating complex, original ideas with clarity, not about gaming detection tools.
So what changed our minds?
Before we get to that, it's important to understand why AI detection scores are not the final word on AI use.
Why AI detectors are far from perfect
They judge writing style, not where ideas came from
AI detectors don‚Äôt know
who
designed the study or thought through the arguments. They tend to flag clear, polished, and well-structured writing, even if every idea came from a human.
They mistake ‚Äúgood writing‚Äù for ‚ÄúAI writing‚Äù
Editing for clarity, flow, or academic tone often
reduces variability
and makes writing
more predictable
. That‚Äôs exactly what detectors look for, which means improved human writing can be wrongly labelled as AI-written.
They are especially unfair to non-native English writers
Writing that‚Äôs grammatically careful or less idiomatic, common among non-native speakers, is more likely to be flagged, even when it‚Äôs entirely human-written.
AI keeps improving, detectors can‚Äôt keep up
As AI models get better at sounding human, detectors fall further behind. There‚Äôs no stable line they can draw between ‚Äúhuman‚Äù and ‚ÄúAI‚Äù writing anymore.
So, why did we build an AI detector?
Because the line between human and AI writing is blurring.
Academics today use AI in many ways‚Äîto brainstorm, structure, edit, and refine. In many cases, the thinking and intent remain fully human, but AI can still shape
how
the writing reads.
Besides, AI influence isn‚Äôt always deliberate. AI-like patterns can enter writing through word processors, autocomplete, grammar suggestions, and summarizers‚Äîtools researchers have used for years.
In this new hybrid writing reality, a simple ‚Äúhuman vs AI‚Äù label doesn‚Äôt reflect how academic writing is actually produced.
That‚Äôs why we built Paperpal‚Äôs AI detector‚Äînot as a shortcut or policing tool, but
to offer a clearer lens
for academics to
see where AI may have influenced their text,
review it in context,
make informed revisions that keep their
voice, intent, and integrity
intact.
Paperpal takes a different approach
Paperpal is built for today's hybrid writing reality.
It analyzes your writing
sentence by sentence
and classifies each one into three clear categories:
Human-written
,
Human‚ÄìAI blend
, or
AI-written
.
These sentence-level signals then roll up into a
document-level score
, giving you a more balanced understanding of the text as a whole.
Importantly, Paperpal‚Äôs AI detector isn‚Äôt built to help you ‚Äúbeat‚Äù detection at a journal or university. It‚Äôs built to help you
take the right next step
: revise specific sentences in your own voice, document your process if needed, add disclosures where appropriate, and submit with confidence.
What makes Paperpal's AI detector dependable‚Äîand complete
It‚Äôs built on¬†100,000+ human and AI scholarly samples¬†from ChatGPT, Claude, and Gemini,
providing¬†more reliable AI¬†detection¬†than¬†generic AI checkers
.
It
uses cross-verifying models¬†to
reduce false positives by over 40%
, delivering¬†research-grade AI¬†detection that can stand up to institutional review.
Its three-band scale highlights¬†hybrid writing¬†to¬†help
assess authenticity with precision
, not guesswork.
It processes your
text ephemerally¬†using¬†multi-level¬†encryption. Your data is never stored or used to train the AI,¬†ensuring
complete confidentiality¬†and security
.
It is continually¬†retrained so it¬†always
stays¬†ahead of¬†any¬†evolving generative¬†AI¬†systems
and emerging writing patterns.
Beyond AI detection, Paperpal offers seamless¬†access to editing, plagiarism, and other¬†features¬†that¬†allow you to revise your paper and ready it for submission‚Äîall in one place.
Institutions use AI detectors to protect academic integrity, not to punish thoughtful use of modern tools. Increasingly, they recognize that AI detection scores are signals, not evidence of misconduct.
Used responsibly, AI detectors create room for transparency and dialogue, not judgment.
That‚Äôs where Paperpal comes in. Our AI tracking and AI detection toolkit help you see what‚Äôs being flagged and why, review it in context, make targeted revisions that keep your voice and intent intact, and submit your work with clarity and transparency.
Happy writing!
Nolita Coelho
VP of Product @Paperpal
